(195, 1, '2014-09-25 01:26:21', '2014-09-25 01:26:21', 'If we say 100% is knowing everything, here is the verdict on my skills...\r\n\r\n[row]\r\n\r\n[column lg="6" md="6" sm="12" xs="12" ]\r\n\r\n<img class="bottompad alignleft wp-image-248 size-full" src="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/HTML5_Logo_512.png" alt="hmtl5" width="80" height="80" />[progressbar value="80" class="htmlfive"  barstyle="progress-striped active" label="HTML, HTML5"]\r\n\r\n<p class="overflow-hidden">I started learning HTML back in 2007 when I made a my own website and some small business websites. Since <b>HMTL5</b> came out its been a revelation to use more semantic html, built in form validation and post media content more easily. </p>\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<img class="bottompad alignleft wp-image-254 size-full" src="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/css3-logo.png" alt="css" width="80" height="80" />[progressbar value="85" class="cssthree"  barstyle="progress-striped active" label="CSS, CSS3"]\r\n\r\n<p class="overflow-hidden">It took me a while to get my head around using CSS, however through projects I learnt it''s beauty. CSS3 offers more options like text-shadow, border-radius, flex-box, calculating sizes.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<img class="bottompad alignleft wp-image-264 size-full" src="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/javascript_logo_.png" alt="javascript" width="80" height="80" />[progressbar value="55" class="jsskills"  barstyle="progress-striped active" label="JavaScript"]\r\n\r\n<div class="overflow-hidden">After completing courses:\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li><a title="code academy" href="http://www.codecademy.com" target="_blank">Code Academy</a></li>\r\n  <li><a href="https://teamtreehouse.com/" target="_blank">Treehouse</a> - this is the course I highly recommend!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n  I''ve managed to think JavaScript. </div>\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<img src="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/responsive.png" class="bottompad alignleft wp-image-264 size-full" alt="responsive" width="80" height="80" />[progressbar value="75" class="responsive-bar"  barstyle="progress-striped active" label="Responsive Design"]\r\n\r\n<p class="overflow-hidden">I understand how responsive design works, through media queries or flex-box. I''ve created my own media queries and used frameworks like <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/" target="_blank">Bootstrap</a>  to assist me.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n[/column]\r\n\r\n[column lg="6" md="6" sm="12" xs="12" ]\r\n\r\n<img class="bottompad alignleft wp-image-276 size-full" src="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/jquery-logo1.jpg" alt="" width="80" height="80" />[progressbar value="65" class="jqskills"  barstyle="progress-striped active" label="jQuery - <em>write less, do more</em>"]\r\n\r\n<p class="overflow-hidden">I love using jQuery and I use whenever possible to make JavaScript more easy to use. </p>\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<img class="bottompad alignleft wp-image-257 size-full" src="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/wp.jpg" alt="" width="80" height="80" />[progressbar value="65" class="wpskills"  barstyle="progress-striped active" label="Wordpress Development"]\r\n\r\n<p class="overflow-hidden">After creating several sites using themes, I decided to design my own theme, which you are looking at now. </p>\r\n\r\n<hr>\r\n\r\n<img class="bottompad alignleft wp-image-278 size-full" src="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/php_01.png" alt="" width="80" height="78" />[progressbar value="25" class="php"  barstyle="progress-striped active" label="PHP"]\r\n\r\n<p class="overflow-hidden">I still have more to learn. I have used PHP to create forms that post emails and of course I use it in Wordpress. </p>\r\n\r\n[/column]\r\n[/row]\r\n\r\n', 'Skills Estimator', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'skills-estimation-meter', '', '', '2015-09-17 12:07:55', '2015-09-17 12:07:55', '', 0, 'http://localhost/jpmwordpress//?page_id=195', 0, 'page', '', 0),
