ntry-title"></h1>\r\n<h1 class="entry-title">Skills</h1>\r\n</header>If we say 100% is knowing everything, here is my verdict on my skills...\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">[row]</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">[column lg="6" md="12" sm="12" xs="12" ]</p>\r\n<img class="bottompad alignleft wp-image-248 size-full" src="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/HTML5_Logo_512.png" alt="" width="80" height="80" />[progressbar value="80" class="htmlfive" barstyle="progress-striped active" label="HTML, HTML5"]\r\n<p class="marginleft">I started learning html back in 2007 when I made a my own website and some small business websites. Since html 5 came out I''ve used the new semantics like &lt;header&gt;, &lt;footer&gt;, &lt;article&gt;, and &lt;section&gt; for some static pages.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="bottompad alignleft wp-image-254 size-full" src="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/css3-logo.png" alt="" width="80" height="80" />[progressbar value="85" class="cssthree" barstyle="progress-striped active" label="CSS, CSS3"]\r\n<p class="marginleft">It took me a while to get my head around using CSS, especially like Pseudo-classes, CSS Combinators (eg descendant, child ), postitioning...but I managed to understand it, mostly through doing projects and using websites like <a href="http://www.w3schools.com" target="_blank">www.w3schools.com</a></p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="bottompad alignleft wp-image-264 size-full" src="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/javascript_logo_.png" alt="" width="80" height="80" />[progressbar value="65" class="jsskills" barstyle="progress-striped active" label="JavaScript"]\r\n<p class="marginleft">After completing the JavaScript courses on <a href="https://teamtreehouse.com" target="_blank">Treehouse</a>, <a title="code academy" href="http://www.codecademy.com" target="_blank">Code Academy</a>, attended several <a title="codebar" href="http://codebar.io/" target="_blank">Codebar </a>events, I started to make some fun web apps like my <a href="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/snap/snap.html" target="_blank">pairs game</a> and <a href="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/decision-maker.html" target="_blank">decision-maker</a>. I also use JS regularly at work for <a href="http://15below.com/" target="_blank">15below</a>.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="bottompad alignleft wp-image-276 size-full" src="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/jquery-logo1.jpg" alt="" width="80" height="80" />[progressbar value="65" class="jqskills" barstyle="progress-striped active" label="jQuery - <em>write less, do more</em>"]\r\n<p class="marginleft">What can I say about jQuery except, I love jQuery, it simplifies JavaScript and makes it easier to do stuff.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="bottompad alignleft wp-image-278 size-full" src="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/php_01.png" alt="" width="80" height="78" />[progressbar value="15" class="php" barstyle="progress-striped active" label="PHP"]\r\n<p class="marginleft">I''m not currently an expert on php but I''ve tweaked php code in making wordpress sites</p>\r\n<p class="marginleft"></p>\r\n<img class="bottompad alignleft wp-image-257 size-full" src="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/wp.jpg" alt="" width="80" height="80" />[progressbar value="75" class="wpskills" barstyle="progress-striped active" label="Wordpress Development"]\r\n<p class="marginleft">First time I used Wordpress I didn''t like it too much, "posts" or "pages"? what do I use? Now, I love it. Its so fast, free and a great introduction to PHP. I''ve made lots of small business sites on Wordpress and of course, this site.</p>\r\n<p class="marginleft">[/column]</p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n[column lg="6" md="12" sm="12" xs="12" ]</p>\r\n<img class="bottompad alignleft wp-image-240 size-full" src="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/pslogo2.jpg" alt="photoshop" width="80" height="78" />[progressbar value="95" class="photoshop" barstyle="progress-striped active" label="Adobe Photoshop"]\r\n<p class="marginleft">I started using Photoshop at University and haven''t stopped, I''ve even helped the Police solve crimes with my Photoshop skills</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="bottompad alignleft wp-image-222 size-full" src="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/Adobe_Illustrator_Icon_CS6-copy.jpg" alt="Adobe_Illustrator_Icon_CS6 copy" width="80" height="78" />[progressbar value="85" class="illustrator" barstyle="progress-striped active" label="Adobe Illustrator"]\r\n<p class="marginleft">I''ve made lots of logos, cutting paths, buttons, mini illustrations and all kinds of lovely things on this baby.</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="bottompad alignleft wp-image-244 size-full" src="http://localhost/jpmwordpress/wp-content/uploads/2014/09/indesign.jpg" alt="indesign" width="80" height="78" />[progressbar value="90" class="indesign" barstyle="progress-striped active" label="Adobe Indesign"]\r\n<p class="marginleft">I love Indesign for creating multipage artworks. Lets be honest - it kicks Quark''s ass. I''ve made calendars, brochures, product catalogues, large format exhibition graphics...too many to mention</p>\r\n<p class="marginleft">[/column]\r\n<br style="text-align: center;" /> [/row]</p>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'Services', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '335-autosave-v1', '', '', '2015-05-10 00:28:03', '2015-05-10 00:28:03', '', 335, 'http://localhost/jpmwordpress//335-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
