(730, 1, '2015-01-07 11:01:15', '2015-01-07 11:01:15', 'I started off as a designer and now I''m moving further into web development.\r\n\r\n<strong>How have I found it?</strong>\r\n\r\nIt''s a very different world moving into web development. Simply put, its tougher. With design, everything is visual and instant. With coding everything needs to be planned and patiently created step by step, the code needs constant testing every step you take. This transition from being a designer to a coder has taken around 2 years and there is still lots to learn.\r\n\r\nMeeting other web developers and freelancers, the question that always comes up is "are you a designer or a coder?". When I reply, "both", I get a surprised reaction. There seems to be a divide in that you are either a designer or coder...<strong>why is that?</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Why don''t more people do both?</strong>\r\n\r\nI''d be interested to hear from any people that have also made the transition from doing graphic design type work to web development. How did you find learning JavaScript and the vast arrays of frameworks that are available to use?\r\n\r\nAll the best, John.', 'Designer to coder', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'designer-to-coder', '', '', '2015-01-07 11:05:08', '2015-01-07 11:05:08', '', 0, 'http://localhost/jpmwordpress//?p=730', 0, 'post', '', 0),
